leads.lead_text: Petals and sepals yellow to greenish, spotted and streaked with red or mauve
Petals and sepals cream or pink-spotted or blotched with dark pink or maroon (rarely wholly pink or white)
Pedicels and ovaries with maroon spots; petals and sepals cream or light pink with heavy maroon blotching; East Gippsland only
Pedicels and ovaries without coloured spots; petals and sepals light rosy pink or white with darker spots or blotches, or rarely wholly pink or white
Perianth segments straight or gently recurved throughout, not strongly recurved near tips, distinctly spotted or blotched
Perianth segments strongly recurved near tips, unspotted, or rather indistinctly spotted or blotched
Flowers bell-shaped, white with heavy pink blotches
Flowers opening widely, pale to dark reddish-pink with heavy darker blotches
Perianth segments white to pale pink with many large darker pink blotches; labellum with blotches; stems usually green
Perianth segments pink with few, or no, darker pink spots; labellum with longitudinal pink stripes; stems usually purplish
